[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class structure**\n\nI'm pondering whether to avoid using define/execute and just focus on toByteArray for computing frames. There's a concern that it still references constructors that haven’t been checked. It might make sense to assert bytes in tests. Should I consider using better public static classes or even nested public static classes within the test? If there’s no constructor, should it default to public? I wonder about the access levels for nested classes too.\n\n**Evaluating Class Loaders**\n\nI'm considering that Class.forName(String) uses the defining loader of the caller, which might include test classes if the library class loader includes them. In Gradle tests, the library and the test app classloader could be the same, but there’s no loader in a native image. In the JVM, the cglib dependency is loaded by the test app loader, so it can access tests. I should probably inspect the coverage report to check for any currently uncovered stats. That might be a good idea!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b6f8a85f17cff860169ef66d9c974819daec2ae45dc2757d4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp72brYCRPdFOB7ywk9o_IxfoAmtm41IRebbRIZXTKs0rtL88sf4yaIBkhJAMaQcT7Y-hkitRVwyPxpFPVUBlrGqw41O1t4GE7rTfayPqsWpKBgcJfffNyaEbBOjJ_tIBLoENynUeGEELoTP3gL0pOItonK5EJEX8xeW-dcPBn-eJPLaruz5NWHWN3dGzpIU_W_zT0sepaJdl2eUUUUizPqMAG6kHDFB81euL7hPPUWaQ6mwv1tjfnJCjnGHQSF2biqOfHSeN-0dgAJ3IJ1hMLAARucOO44dNSb0EIhtZ2QvStabXqSrPuCrE6BBlSRimVqJvKEz2-0UG0gC05xK1Bg49zgXwbU5RL6CysAq-wgZAtl0zAg-bGCMpFfqrEAOa3LidRxSbL7ImIN6ti4hkVDHgt7J8-nTGVHqtWiACnQgHcO3UjYlR370V3gatiy3En9iYcbkUjLlnmua8DhROiouY3D2D-XlXJDzrBESPM363uMaccdBGW2TrQjVF2OTCZdMgyCFLSqpuac5wz5HlnJMnvA4aG2uJUuvYtkEO0BVKSIiFfW46MaU5F4PqbdpsyKArCMXuRZ7qmhqjUzf-M7ZWC10Dwl4ps5rHEPMFJS3r_VTDU18hCfY5eK47zg_XlnSmoc_KgMQrL27jGtvMaqvg-gvhfVaZNX-5kI643jh2lziDu1BelZdvEj-an_C-ga-NgFZrgALiyE7RhIFMAbsKlYV9Ct9OAA